Very Good Camera with lots of Features.
I ordered this camera from flipkart at 30.5k, and it was delivered very promptly in efficient packaging. After using it for almost a month now, I find it to be a sound choice. There are several compatible lenses for this camera, and the body itself is sturdy enough to be durable and last long. My initial buying dilemma was between Nikon D5100 and this one. You can't go wrong with either of the two. Both are equally capable models. Coming to the Canon 600D, the following are some of my observations: 1. The Camera performs well in all modes, with no noticeable degradation of IQ between 18 and 55mm. It starts up lightening fast. By the time you flip the on-switch and look through the viewfinder, it will be ready. 2. The camera has been designed with large hands in mind. I am able to hold it very comfortably. 3. There are extra buttons on the back that prove very useful when quick changes are needed. 4. Focusing is slightly noisy, but reasonably fast. 5. Contrary to so many reviews, I have confirmed that there is NO inbuilt AF motor. This matters very little anyway, as almost all Canon Lenses come with in built motors. 6. It is recommended to use the viewfinder with this model (if you are not already accustomed to this). There is a live view mode available, but it is not at all the way to use a dSLR 7. The Articulated display is a god-send. Has proven very useful in many situations (when using live view, or to set up the shot at odd angles) 8. The battery is quite capable of taking 600-700 shots in one cycle (provided you dont waste too much power reviewing each shot and using live view). There are many more things that I could put here, but that would be redundant, as they are already there in several other reviews. All in all, this is an awesome camera to start with for Amateurs, and can be used for intermediate and even professional photography.
