I am writing this review after purchasing this camera one month back and using it for last 1 month. As already mentioned in earlier posts this camera takes great pictures. The features provided are decent (I personally use the manual feature, have not used the presets quite often). The Auto+ feature is really very nice. The feel of 600D in hand is quite good, it is bigger then Nikon models of the same range. Low light photography is not as good as Nikon. After 3200 ISO you will see noise. The video mode is fantastic in 600D, you have full control on the functions. With this camera and a good software you can easily make a short flim. I do not see any limitation on 600D. The colors are vibrant and detailed. I have shifted from canon s5IS (semi slr). So, missing the long zoom lens of s5IS (as I have only the kit lens). I would like to discuss about the 18-55 kit lens (as I have not found any detailed description of the same). If you are shifting from any semi-slr cameras or long zoom camera you will not get any zoom nearer to them in 18-55 kit lens. Having said so, you will still have some decent zooming experience. I believe, the kit lens takes best portrait shots at 50mm (my personal feeling, might be wrong). So, incase you are taking a portrait shot, try to keep it at 50 mm and adjust your position. The lens smooth when you move from 18 to 55. It is a bit noisy when using the AF (auto focus). As it has 18mm, you will have a very good wide angel for shots. I have got full Taj Mahal shot from quite near. In general, it is a good lens which takes decent photographs. Personally I feel you should have 18-55 lens in your collection if you do not want to invest in 2 - 3 different lenses. Again, if you want to make video use the kit lens at 50mm (If you do not want to buy the 50mm prime lens also known as plastic wounder.) The lens takes good video. Overall 600D is fantastic for beginners as first dslr camera. Use the kit lens to set your hand on dslr. There are lots of features which will keep you busy for few months. Regarding flipkart delivery (ws retail for my case) has been pleasant. Took few days to reach me. Packing was very good and the free accessories on the offer was also very good. One final note if you are not getting a dslr bag with the camera, please don't forget to buy the same.
