Just wanted to give a short review about this great SLR camera. With Flipkart's pricing, I was way too confused between Nikon D5100 and Canon 600D - you can't go wrong with either of them, though Nikon's colors tend to be on the punchy side. Most prosumer grade DSLRs have a plethora of options and tricks, but all that matters the most is how you frame and compose your image. Based on my observations: 1. Image quality - excellent resolution 2. Image colors - a little dull (ever so lightly though) in default mode, but just tweak a notch up in custom picture settings, you'll be awed! 3. Burst speed - pretty good! I tried it with AI Servo focus mode on my 11 month old son always on the move, and the results are fantastic! 4. Image noise - yes, it's present at 1600 ISO, but why would you even shoot beyond 800 ISO in these mid-range DSLRs? 5. Build quality - Made in Taiwan, and feels pretty solid except for the SDCard and Battery doors. Would have been happier with a 'Made in Japan', but it's ok, we're a third world country! 6. 18-55 kit lens - I wish Canon gave a lens as sharp as the ones that come with Sony SLTs. No comparison here, the SLTs' kit lens are way better. It might sound subjective, but you be the judge 7. Video quality and options - awesome at this price point What could have been better? (note: these are not cons) 1. Auto focus on live view (contrast detect) - pathetic, and I'm more convinced to use the optical viewfinder :) 2. Missing proximity sensor under the view-finder (the 550D had this!!) 3. Mode dials do not rotate 360 deg. My Canon S5IS rotates perpetually, which is good 4. Bundling an HDMI cable would have been a nice touch Note 1: I didn't buy from Flipkart for 2 reasons. 1. Much lower price at a local store near my place. 2. Didn't want any of their freebies ('ll buy them separately, later) Note 2: WARRANTY registration on Canon Edge. When I tried to register my camera, it said 'Serial number not found'. I panicked and even went to the lengths of thinking that it could be a smuggled product as I bought for cheap :( Then after digging around, wrote a mail to admin@canonedge.com with a screenshot of my invoice, and I was able to register the product after 24 hours. @Kunal Puri - this answers your question? You can lower your eyebrows now ;)
THE PRODUCT: It was a toss up between the 650D and the older 600D and I finally went with the 600D after reading reams of pages and forums on the two cameras. I needed something for video that wouldn't break the bank and the Digic 5 on the 650D didn't convince me enough to shell out the extra cash. I'm happy to say I believe I made the right decision. The 600D performs beautifully, especially with a 64GB SDXC card thrown into the mix. I quickly added a 50mm prime lens and the results are sheer poetry. One week into receiving the camera I've already got two other colleagues to place orders for theirs. The rest of the good stuff on the 600D is amply available online and there's little else I can add that others on this page and elsewhere haven't already said. THE DELIVERY: I was sorely let down with this transaction. Maybe I have high expectations from Flipkart who've had a stellar track record with all my past transactions. So much so that I had switched from another popular online portal for all my purchases. The initial shipping estimate for the product was 5 days. This itself is too high at a time when retailers are delivering products in two days or less. Ironically, the web page for the product promises that it will be "Delivered in 2-3 business days". A day after the due date passed I was asked to wait another 3 days which is when I decided to cancel the order and just get my camera from somewhere else. I'm not sure whether to credit Flipkart with swinging into action and having the camera delivered that very day or to point a finger at them and say, your customer shouldn't have to come to cancelling his order before proactive action is taken. Either way, my rating here is for the product and not the service. Incidentally, while trying to register the camera online I was told by the website that the serial number is not recognised. Another reason to raise eye-brows?
